          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>Jobs and Opportunity Bonus Tax Credit Act of 2014 or the JOB Tax Credit Act - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow&nbsp;employers who employ not more than 500 full-time employees during the taxable year a business-related tax credit equal to the lesser of: (1) 50% of the job training program&nbsp;expenditures for a full-time&nbsp;employee participating in a qualified training program, or (2) $5,000. Terminates such credit after 2017.</p>]]></text>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2014-05-13T18:53:20Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <actionDate>2014-03-11</actionDate>
          <updateDate>2014-03-11T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
    </summaries>
